<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1238,1804]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
Valves very delicate, 82–92 µm long, 5.5–6.0 µm wide, practically parallel-sided and straight for most of their length, becoming sigmoid near acute apex. Raphe sternum straight except near apices, where it first curves to dorsal side and then recurves on a strongly eccentric and sigmoid course. Striation (Fig. 26): transverse striae circa 
<quantity box="[1263,1363,1310,1336]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.699" metricValueMax="4.826" metricValueMin="4.572" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" unit="in" value="18.5" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="18.0">18–19 in</quantity>
10 µm, longitudinal striae circa 
<quantity box="[411,512,1346,1373]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.144" metricValueMax="9.398" metricValueMin="8.89" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" unit="in" value="36.0" valueMax="37.0" valueMin="35.0">35–37 in</quantity>
10 µm, becoming irregular at the apices (Fig. 27). No hyaline central area visible, central raphe node minute and elongated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="76" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1238,1804]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1418,1444]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet baculum (“staff”) is chosen to describe the typical reversed curvature of the raphe sternum at the apices.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1238,1804]" box="[189,592,1490,1516]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,281,1490,1516]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Habitat</emphasis>
:—Littoral-marine, benthic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="76" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1238,1804]" box="[189,581,1526,1553]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,1526,1552]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<typeStatus box="[368,427,1527,1553]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Type</typeStatus>
locality only.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1238,1804]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,348,1562,1588]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Observations</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herwig &amp; Sterrenburg" authorityYear="2014" box="[384,612,1562,1589]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Pleurosigmataceae" genus="Gyrosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="baculum">
<emphasis box="[384,612,1562,1589]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Gyrosigma baculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cleve" authorityYear="1894" baseAuthorityName="W. Sm." box="[768,944,1563,1589]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Pleurosigmataceae" genus="Gyrosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="tenuissimum">
<emphasis box="[768,944,1563,1589]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">G. tenuissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in two independent characters: the different course of the raphe sternum and stria density. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herwig &amp; Sterrenburg" authorityYear="2014" box="[699,931,1598,1625]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Pleurosigmataceae" genus="Gyrosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="baculum">
<emphasis box="[699,931,1598,1625]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Gyrosigma baculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
somewhat resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricard (1975: 209" authorityName="Ricard" authorityYear="1975" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Pleurosigmataceae" genus="Gyrosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="uncinatum">
<emphasis box="[1197,1451,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Gyrosigma uncinatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ricard, M." box="[136,346,1634,1661]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" pagination="201 - 229" refId="ref5510" refString="Ricard, M. (1975) Quelques diatomees nouvelles de Tahiti decrites en microscopie photonique et electronique a balayage. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Botanique, 3 e ser., no 326, 23: 201 - 229." type="journal article" year="1975">Ricard (1975: 209</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, fig. 3) in valve contour and raphe sternum course but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ricard" authorityYear="1975" box="[977,1131,1635,1661]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Pleurosigmataceae" genus="Gyrosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="uncinatum">
<emphasis box="[977,1131,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">G. uncinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has much coarser (
<quantity box="[1356,1415,1634,1661]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.81" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" unit="in" value="15.0">15 in</quantity>
10 µm) transverse striae, a value incompatible with the stria density of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herwig &amp; Sterrenburg" authorityYear="2014" box="[914,1046,1670,1697]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Pleurosigmataceae" genus="Gyrosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="baculum">
<emphasis box="[914,1046,1670,1697]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">G. baculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. No 
<typeStatus box="[1105,1153,1671,1697]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">type</typeStatus>
specimens for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ricard" authorityYear="1975" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Pleurosigmataceae" genus="Gyrosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="uncinatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Gyrosigma uncinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been deposited in PC. No specimens have been isolated for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herwig &amp; Sterrenburg" authorityYear="2014" box="[992,1122,1706,1733]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Pleurosigmataceae" genus="Gyrosigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="baculum">
<emphasis box="[992,1122,1706,1733]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">G. baculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for SEM examination as it is very rare in the 
<typeStatus box="[308,356,1743,1769]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">type</typeStatus>
material, but the LM findings of raphe sternum course and stria densities already permit separation from the described species.
</paragraph>
